{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"231af601-40a9-4139-b704-32a5ef859027","content":"\n\nHere's a quick overview of common choices:\n\n## .NET (`dotnet new webapi`)\nAuth options: `--auth` flag with:\n- **None** (default)\n- **Individual** – ASP.NET Identity / local accounts\n- **IndividualB2C** – Azure AD B2C\n- **SingleOrg** – Azure AD (single tenant)\n- **MultiOrg** – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- **Windows** – Windows/NTLM/Kerberos\n\n## Node.js / Express\nUse `express-generator` then add middleware:\n- **Passport.js** (JWT, OAuth2, Local, etc.)\n- **express-jwt** + **jwks-rsa** for token validation\n\n## Python / FastAPI\n- **OAuth2PasswordBearer** (built-in)\n- **python-jose** for JWT\n\n## Java / Spring Boot\nUse Spring Initializr with **Spring Security**:\n- OAuth2 Resource Server, OAuth2 Client, LDAP\n\n---\n\nFor a **.NET Web API** specifically, the fastest start is:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific framework and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af932838-d48c-4dcf-8360-38b4b6114537","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular frameworks.","outputTokens":354},"id":"10732dfd-a802-47c2-a23f-d8f521df56e5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:52:37.707Z","parentId":"32ffe1b8-c6b9-4c27-a321-b7a92cb5161e"}
